'''G.N. Panicker''' (born 1937<ref name="Lal1992">{{cite book|last=Lal|first=Mohan|title=Encyclopaedia of Indian Literature: Sasay to Zorgot|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KnPoYxrRfc0C&pg=PA4056|accessdate=26 April 2018|year=1992|publisher=Sahitya Akademi|isbn=9788126012213|pages=4056–}}</ref>) is an Indian author who won the [[Kerala]] Sahitya Akademi award for short stories in 1982 for his book ''Neeruravakalkku Oru Geetham''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kerala.gov.in/literacy-awards|title=Literary Awards - Government of Kerala, India|accessdate=26 April 2018}}</ref> He won the [[P. Kesavadev]] Literary Award in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/Kesavadev-awards/article14490297.ece|title=Kesavadev awards - KERALA - The Hindu|work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=26 April 2018}}</ref> Panicker is also involved with highlighting works by other Tamil writers, producing a booklet containing excerpts from the works of eight authors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/booklet-on-tamil-writers-released/article5031265.ece|title=Booklet on Tamil writers released - KERALA - The Hindu|work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=26 April 2018}}</ref>

