{{Infobox saint | name = Muhammad Mohsin Bekas | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | titles = '''درگاه بيدل بيڪس''' |birth_date = January 31, 1859 A.D. ( 26 Jumada II 1275 A.H.) |birth_place = [[Rohri]], [[Sindh]][[Pakistan]] |death_date = August 1, 1881 A.D. (5 Ramadan 1298 A.H.) |death_place = [[Rohri]] | venerated_in = [[Islam]], [[Hinduism]] | influences = [[Qadir Bux Bedil]] | influenced = | major_work = [[Diwan-e- Bekas]] | tradition = [[Poetry]] }}
'''Muhammad Mohsin''' (1859–1882) was a [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] poet,<ref>{{cite book |title=Encyclopaedia of Muslim Biography: Muh-R |last=Singh |first=Nagendra Kr |page=47 |year=2001 |publisher=A.P.H. Publishing |isbn=978-81-7648-234-9 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Encyclopaedia of Indian Literature: K to Navalram |last=Datta |first=Amaresh |page=2775 |year=1987 |publisher=[[Sahitya Akademi]] |oclc=16957285 }}</ref>, better known by his [[Pen name|nom-de-plume]] '''Bekas'''. He was the son of Faqeer [[Qadir Bux Bedil|Bedil]] and the first follower of his school of thought in poetry. They are buried at the same place so the shrine is commonly known as the shrine of Bedil and Bekas.
