* In [[telecommunication]], the term '''multiple homing''' has the following meanings: ** [[telephone]] systems, the [[electrical connection|connection]] of a [[terminal (telecommunication)|terminal]] [[Facility (telecommunications)|facility]] so that it can be served by one or several [[telephone exchange|switching centers]]. Multiple homing may use a single [[telephone number|directory number]]. ** In telephone systems, the connection of a terminal facility to more than one [[telephone exchange|switching center]] by separate [[Access in telecommunications|access]] lines. Separate directory numbers are applicable to each switching center accessed.
* In [[military]], such as [[Missile]]s and [[loitering munition]]s, it is ability of a single weapon system or projectile to select, focus and simultaneously engage multiple targets.
